\n    - Technical assessment\\n    - Behavioral assessment\\n    - Strengths and weaknesses\\n    - Final recommendation and scoring breakdown\\n\\nFinal output: Evaluation report of candidate in .txt\\n\\n---\\n# **Context from Upstream Tasks**\\nTask task1:\\n  Objective: Perform resume-job match analysis using parsed data, producing a match score and key alignment points\\n  Result: ```json\\n{\\n  \\\"resume_job_match_analysis\\\": {\\n    \\\"overall_match_score\\\": 85,\\n    \\\"key_alignment_points\\\": [\\n      \\\"The candidate has a Bachelor's degree in Computer Science, matching the job requirement.\\\",\\n      \\\"The candidate has 3+ years of experience as a Software Engineer, meeting the job's experience level.\\\",\\n      \\\"The candidate possesses key skills such as Java, Python, SQL, REST APIs, Agile, Git, Data Structures, and Algorithms, which align with the job description.\\\",\\n      \\\"The candidate has experience developing and maintaining Java-based web applications, which is relevant to the job's responsibilities.\\\",\\n      \\\"The candidate has experience implementing REST APIs, matching a specific requirement in the job description.\\\",\\n      \\\"The candidate has experience with unit and integration testing, fulfilling another job requirement.\\\",\\n      \\\"The candidate's experience with Agile development aligns with the job requirements.\\\"\\n    ],\\n    \\\"gaps\\\": [\\n      \\\"The job description mentions Cloud Computing (AWS/Azure/GCP), while the candidate only lists AWS. Experience with Azure or GCP is not explicitly mentioned.\\\",\\n      \\\"Communication and Problem-Solving skills are listed in the job description but are not explicitly detailed in the candidate's skills section. While implicitly demonstrated through experience, direct evidence is lacking.\\\"\\n    ],\\n    \\\"suitability_assessment\\\": \\\"The candidate is highly suitable for the Software Engineer position. Their education, experience, and skills closely match the job requirements. The candidate demonstrates proficiency in the required technical areas and has relevant project experience. Addressing the gaps in Cloud Computing beyond AWS and emphasizing Communication and Problem-Solving skills during the interview will provide a more complete picture.\\\"\\n  }\\n}\\n```\\nTask task3:\\n  Objective: Evaluate candidate responses for relevance, depth, confidence, and technical accuracy, producing per-question scores\\n  Result: ```json\\n{\\n  \\\"candidate_evaluation\\\": {\\n    \\\"technical\\\": [\\n      {\\n        \\\"question\\\": \\\"Describe your experience with Java and Spring Boot. Can you provide an example of a challenging problem you solved using these technologies?\\\",\\n        \\\"candidate_response\\\": \\\"I have 5 years of experience with Java and Spring Boot. In my previous role, I worked on a microservices architecture. A challenging problem I faced was optimizing the performance of a service that was experiencing high latency under peak load.\\\",\\n        \\\"relevance_score\\\": 5,\\n        \\\"depth_score\\\": 4,\\n        \\\"confidence_score\\\": 5,\\n        \\\"technical_accuracy_score\\\": 5,\\n        \\\"follow_up_responses\\\": [\\n          {\\n            \\\"follow_up_question\\\": \\\"How did you approach debugging the problem?\\\",\\n            \\\"candidate_response\\\": \\\"I used profiling tools to identify the bottleneck, which turned out to be inefficient database queries and excessive object creation.\\\",\\n            \\\"relevance_score\\\": 5,\\n            \\\"depth_score\\\": 4,\\n            \\\"confidence_score\\\": 5,\\n            \\\"technical_accuracy_score\\\": 5\\n          },\\n          {\\n            \\\"follow_up_question\\\": \\\"What were the key design decisions you made?\\\",\\n            \\\"candidate_response\\\": \\\"We implemented connection pooling, optimized the database queries using indexes, and reduced object creation by caching frequently accessed data.\\\",\\n            \\\"relevance_score\\\": 5,\\n            \\\"depth_score\\\": 5,\\n            \\\"confidence_score\\\": 5,\\n            \\\"technical_accuracy_score\\\": 5\\n          },\\n          {\\n            \\\"follow_up_question\\\": \\\"How did you ensure the solution was scalable and maintainable?\\\",\\n            \\\"candidate_response\\\": \\\"We used established design patterns, wrote unit tests, and implemented monitoring and alerting to ensure the service remained scalable and maintainable.\\\",\\n            \\\"relevance_score\\\": 5,\\n            \\\"depth_score\\\": 4,\\n            \\\"confidence_score\\\": 5,\\n            \\\"technical_accuracy_score\\\": 5\\n          }\\n        ]\\n      },\\n      {\\n        \\\"question\\\": \\\"Explain the difference between a HashMap and a TreeMap in Java. When would you use one over the other?\\\",\\n        \\\"candidate_response\\\": \\\"A HashMap is based on hashing and provides constant-time average complexity for insertion, deletion, and retrieval. A TreeMap is based on a red-black tree and provides logarithmic time complexity for these operations. HashMap does not guarantee any ordering, while TreeMap maintains elements in sorted order based on their keys. You'd use a TreeMap when you need to iterate over the keys in sorted order.\\\",\\n        \\\"relevance_score\\\": 5,\\n        \\\"depth_score\\\": 5,\\n        \\\"confidence_score\\\": 5,\\n        \\\"technical_accuracy_score\\\": 5,\\n        \\\"follow_up_responses\\\": [\\n          {\\n            \\\"follow_up_question\\\": \\\"How do these data structures handle collisions?\\\",\\n            \\\"candidate_response\\\": \\\"HashMap uses separate chaining or open addressing to handle collisions. TreeMap, being a tree-based structure, inherently avoids collisions by maintaining the sorted order.\\\",\\n            \\\"relevance_score\\\": 5,\\n            \\\"depth_score\\\": 4,\\n            \\\"confidence_score\\\": 5,\\n            \\\"technical_accuracy_score\\\": 5\\n          },\\n          {\\n            \\\"follow_up_question\\\": \\\"What is the time complexity for common operations like insertion and retrieval in each?\\\",\\n            \\\"candidate_response\\\": \\\"HashMap offers O(1) on average and O(n) in the worst case for insertion and retrieval. TreeMap provides O(log n) for both insertion and retrieval.\\\",\\n            \\\"relevance_score\\\": 5,\\n            \\\"depth_score\\\": 5,\\n            \\\"confidence_score\\\": 5,\\n            \\\"technical_accuracy_score\\\": 5\\n          },\\n          {\\n            \\\"follow_up_question\\\": \\\"Can you describe a real-world scenario where TreeMap would be more suitable than HashMap?\\\",\\n            \\\"candidate_response\\\": \\\"A TreeMap would be more suitable in a scenario where you need to maintain a sorted list of items, like a leaderboard in a game or a phone directory.\\\",\\n            \\\"relevance_score\\\": 5,\\n            \\\"depth_score\\\": 4,\\n            \\\"confidence_score\\\": 5,\\n            \\\"technical_accuracy_score\\\": 5\\n          }\\n        ]\\n      },\\n      {\\n        \\\"question\\\": \\\"Describe your experience with REST APIs. What are some best practices you follow when designing and implementing them?\\\",\\n        \\\"candidate_response\\\": \\\"I have designed and implemented REST APIs using Spring Boot for various projects. Some best practices I follow include using proper HTTP methods, designing resource-oriented endpoints, using HATEOAS, and implementing proper versioning and documentation.\\\",\\n        \\\"relevance_score\\\": 5,\\n        \\\"depth_score\\\": 4,\\n        \\\"confidence_score\\\": 5,\\n        \\\"technical_accuracy_score\\\": 5,\\n        \\\"follow_up_responses\\\": [\\n          {\\n            \\\"follow_up_question\\\": \\\"How do you handle authentication and authorization in your APIs?\\\",\\n            \\\"candidate_response\\\": \\\"I use JWT (JSON Web Tokens) for authentication and RBAC (Role-Based Access Control) for authorization. I also implement rate limiting and input validation to protect the APIs.\\\",\\n            \\\"relevance_score\\\": 5,\\n            \\\"depth_score\\\": 4,\\n            \\\"confidence_score\\\": 5,\\n            \\\"technical_accuracy_score\\\": 5\\n          },\\n          {\\n            \\\"follow_up_question\\\": \\\"What are some common API design patterns you've used?\\\",\\n            \\\"candidate_response\\\": \\\"I've used patterns like the Command pattern for executing actions, the Factory pattern for creating API clients, and the Strategy pattern for handling different API versions.\\\",\\n            \\\"relevance_score\\\": 4,\\n            \\\"depth_score\\\": 3,\\n            \\\"confidence_score\\\": 4,\\n            \\\"technical_accuracy_score\\\": 4\\n          },\\n          {\\n            \\\"follow_up_question\\\": \\\"How do you ensure your APIs are secure and performant?\\\",\\n            \\\"candidate_response\\\": \\\"I use HTTPS, validate inputs, sanitize data, and implement rate limiting to ensure security. For performance, I use caching, connection pooling, and asynchronous processing.\\\",\\n            \\\"relevance_score\\\": 5,\\n            \\\"depth_score\\\": 4,\\n            \\\"confidence_score\\\": 5,\\n            \\\"technical_accuracy_score\\\": 5\\n          }\\n        ]\\n      },\\n      {\\n        \\\"question\\\": \\\"Explain your experience with SQL. Can you describe a time when you had to optimize a slow-running query?\\\",\\n        \\\"candidate_response\\\": \\\"I have extensive experience with SQL. In one project, a query that retrieved data for a dashboard was taking over 5 minutes to execute. This was unacceptable.\\\",\\n        \\\"relevance_score\\\": 5,\\n        \\\"depth_score\\\": 4,\\n        \\\"confidence_score\\\": 5,\\n        \\\"technical_accuracy_score\\\": 5,\\n        \\\"follow_up_responses\\\": [\\n          {\\n            \\\"follow_up_question\\\": \\\"What tools did you use to identify the bottleneck?\\\",\\n            \\\"candidate_response\\\": \\\"I used the database's query execution plan tool to identify the bottleneck. It showed that a full table scan was occurring because of missing indexes.\\\",\\n            \\\"relevance_score\\\": 5,\\n            \\\"depth_score\\\": 5,\\n            \\\"confidence_score\\\": 5,\\n            \\\"technical_accuracy_score\\\": 5\\n          },\\n          {\\n            \\\"follow_up_question\\\": \\\"What specific techniques did you use to optimize the query?\\\",\\n            \\\"candidate_response\\\": \\\"I added indexes to the columns used in the WHERE clause and JOIN conditions. I also rewrote the query to avoid using functions in the WHERE clause.\\\",\\n            \\\"relevance_score\\\": 5,\\n            \\\"depth_score\\\": 5,\\n            \\\"confidence_score\\\": 5,\\n            \\\"technical_accuracy_score\\\": 5\\n          },\\n          {\\n            \\\"follow_up_question\\\": \\\"How did you measure the performance improvement?\\\",\\n            \\\"candidate_response\\\": \\\"After applying the optimizations, the query execution time dropped from over 5 minutes to under 1 second.\\\",\\n            \\\"relevance_score\\\": 5,\\n            \\\"depth_score\\\": 5,\\n            \\\"confidence_score\\\": 5,\\n            \\\"technical_accuracy_score\\\": 5\\n          }\\n        ]\\n      },\\n      {\\n        \\\"question\\\": \\\"Describe your experience with cloud computing platforms like AWS, Azure, or GCP. What services have you used, and for what purposes?\\\",\\n        \\\"candidate_response\\\": \\\"I have experience with AWS. I've used services like EC2 for compute, S3 for storage, RDS for databases, and Lambda for serverless functions.\\\",\\n        \\\"relevance_score\\\": 5,\\n        \\\"depth_score\\\": 4,\\n        \\\"confidence_score\\\": 5,\\n        \\\"technical_accuracy_score\\\": 5,\\n        \\\"follow_up_responses\\\": [\\n          {\\n            \\\"follow_up_question\\\": \\\"How have you used cloud services to improve scalability and reliability?\\\",\\n            \\\"candidate_response\\\": \\\"I've used EC2 Auto Scaling and Elastic Load Balancing to automatically scale the application based on traffic and ensure high availability. I've also used S3 for storing static assets and CloudFront for content delivery.\\\",\\n            \\\"relevance_score\\\": 5,\\n            \\\"depth_score\\\": 4,\\n            \\\"confidence_score\\\": 5,\\n            \\\"technical_accuracy_score\\\": 5\\n          },\\n          {\\n            \\\"follow_up_question\\\": \\\"What are some of the cost optimization strategies you've employed in the cloud?\\\",\\n            \\\"candidate_response\\\": \\\"I've used reserved instances, spot instances, and auto-scaling to optimize costs. I've also implemented cost monitoring and alerting to identify and address cost inefficiencies.\\\",\\n            \\\"relevance_score\\\": 5,\\n            \\\"depth_score\\\": 4,\\n            \\\"confidence_score\\\": 5,\\n            \\\"technical_accuracy_score\\\": 5\\n          },\\n          {\\n            \\\"follow_up_question\\\": \\\"How do you approach security in the cloud environment?\\\",\\n            \\\"candidate_response\\\": \\\"I use IAM roles and policies to control access to resources. I also use security groups to restrict network traffic and regularly audit security configurations.\\\",\\n            \\\"relevance_score\\\": 5,\\n            \\\"depth_score\\\": 4,\\n            \\\"confidence_score\\\": 5,\\n            \\\"technical_accuracy_score\\\": 5\\n          }\\n        ]\\n      },\\n      {\\n        \\\"question\\\": \\\"Explain the concept of Agile development methodologies. What is your experience working in Agile teams?\\\",\\n        \\\"candidate_response\\\": \\\"Agile is an iterative approach to software development that emphasizes collaboration, flexibility, and customer feedback. I have worked in Agile teams using Scrum and Kanban.\\\",\\n        \\\"relevance_score\\\": 5,\\n        \\\"depth_score\\\": 4,\\n        \\\"confidence_score\\\": 5,\\n        \\\"technical_accuracy_score\\\": 5,\\n        \\\"follow_up_responses\\\": [\\n          {\\n            \\\"follow_up_question\\\": \\\"Describe your role in the Agile team and your responsibilities.\\\",\\n            \\\"candidate_response\\\": \\\"I was a software engineer responsible for developing and testing features, participating in sprint planning and reviews, and collaborating with other team members.\\\",\\n            \\\"relevance_score\\\": 5,\\n            \\\"depth_score\\\": 4,\\n            \\\"confidence_score\\\": 5,\\n            \\\"technical_accuracy_score\\\": 5\\n          },\\n          {\\n            \\\"follow_up_question\\\": \\\"How do you handle conflicts or disagreements within an Agile team?\\\",\\n            \\\"candidate_response\\\": \\\"I try to understand the other person's perspective, communicate my own viewpoint clearly, and work towards a mutually agreeable solution. If necessary, I involve the Scrum Master or team lead to mediate.\\\",\\n            \\\"relevance_score\\\": 5,\\n            \\\"depth_score\\\": 4,\\n            \\\"confidence_score\\\": 5,\\n            \\\"technical_accuracy_score\\\": 5\\n          },\\n          {\\n            \\\"follow_up_question\\\": \\\"What are some of the challenges you've faced working in an Agile environment and how did you overcome them?\\\",\\n            \\\"candidate_response\\\": \\\"One challenge was dealing with changing requirements during a sprint. I addressed this by working closely with the product owner to prioritize and clarify the requirements, and by breaking down the work into smaller, manageable tasks.\\\",\\n            \\\"relevance_score\\\": 5,\\n            \\\"depth_score\\\": 4,\\n            \\\"confidence_score\\\": 5,\\n            \\\"technical_accuracy_score\\\": 5\\n          }\\n        ]\\n      }\\n    ],\\n    \\\"behavioral\\\": [\\n      {\\n        \\\"question\\\": \\\"Tell me about a time you had to work with a difficult team member. How did you handle the situation?\\\",\\n        \\\"candidate_response\\\": \\\"In a previous project, I worked with a team member who was consistently negative and uncooperative. This was affecting team morale and productivity.\\\",\\n        \\\"relevance_score\\\": 5,\\n        \\\"depth_score\\\": 4,\\n        \\\"confidence_score\\\": 5,\\n        \\\"follow_up_responses\\\": [\\n          {\\n            \\\"follow_up_question\\\": \\\"What was the specific issue that made the team member difficult to work with?\\\",\\n            \\\"candidate_response\\\": \\\"The team member would often criticize other people's ideas, refuse to participate in discussions, and complain about the workload.\\\",\\n            \\\"relevance_score\\\": 5,\\n            \\\"depth_score\\\": 4,\\n            \\\"confidence_score\\\": 5\\n          },\\n          {\\n            \\\"follow_up_question\\\": \\\"What steps did you take to address the situation?\\\",\\n            \\\"candidate_response\\\": \\\"I spoke to the team member privately to understand their concerns. I also tried to find common ground and build a positive working relationship. Additionally, I encouraged the team to provide constructive feedback.\\\",\\n            \\\"relevance_score\\\": 5,\\n            \\\"depth_score\\\": 4,\\n            \\\"confidence_score\\\": 5\\n          },\\n          {\\n            \\\"follow_up_question\\\": \\\"What was the outcome, and what did you learn from the experience?\\\",\\n            \\\"candidate_response\\\": \\\"The team member's attitude improved after our conversation, and the team's overall productivity increased. I learned the importance of open communication and empathy when dealing with difficult people.\\\",\\n            \\\"relevance_score\\\": 5,\\n            \\\"depth_score\\\": 4,\\n            \\\"confidence_score\\\": 5\\n          }\\n        ]\\n      },\\n      {\\n        \\\"question\\\": \\\"Describe a situation where you had to learn a new technology or skill quickly. How did you approach it?\\\",\\n        \\\"candidate_response\\\": \\\"I had to learn React.js in a short timeframe for a new project.\\\",\\n        \\\"relevance_score\\\": 5,\\n        \\\"depth_score\\\": 3,\\n        \\\"confidence_score\\\": 5,\\n        \\\"follow_up_responses\\\": [\\n          {\\n            \\\"follow_up_question\\\": \\\"What resources did you use to learn the new technology or skill?\\\",\\n            \\\"candidate_response\\\": \\\"I used online courses, documentation, and tutorials. I also sought help from experienced colleagues.\\\",\\n            \\\"relevance_score\\\": 5,\\n            \\\"depth_score\\\": 4,\\n            \\\"confidence_score\\\": 5\\n          },\\n          {\\n            \\\"follow_up_question\\\": \\\"How did you apply what you learned to a real-world project?\\\",\\n            \\\"candidate_response\\\": \\\"I built a prototype application using React.js to gain hands-on experience.\\\",\\n            \\\"relevance_score\\\": 5,\\n            \\\"depth_score\\\": 4,\\n            \\\"confidence_score\\\": 5\\n          },\\n          {\\n            \\\"follow_up_question\\\": \\\"What challenges did you face, and how did you overcome them?\\\",\\n            \\\"candidate_response\\\": \\\"Understanding the component lifecycle was challenging. I overcame this by experimenting with different components and debugging issues.\\\",\\n            \\\"relevance_score\\\": 5,\\n            \\\"depth_score\\\": 4,\\n            \\\"confidence_score\\\": 5\\n          }\\n        ]\\n      },\\n      {\\n        \\\"question\\\": \\\"Tell me about a time you made a mistake at work. How did you handle it, and what did you learn from it?\\\",\\n        \\\"candidate_response\\\": \\\"I accidentally deleted a production database table.\\\",\\n        \\\"relevance_score\\\": 5,\\n        \\\"depth_score\\\": 3,\\n        \\\"confidence_score\\\": 5,\\n        \\\"follow_up_responses\\\": [\\n          {\\n            \\\"follow_up_question\\\": \\\"What were the consequences of the mistake?\\\",\\n            \\\"candidate_response\\\": \\\"The application was down, and users were unable to access their data.\\\",\\n            \\\"relevance_score\\\": 5,\\n            \\\"depth_score\\\": 4,\\n            \\\"confidence_score\\\": 5\\n          },\\n          {\\n            \\\"follow_up_question\\\": \\\"What steps did you take to rectify the situation?\\\",\\n            \\\"candidate_response\\\": \\\"I restored the table from a backup. Then, I worked with the team to prevent this from happening again.\\\",\\n            \\\"relevance_score\\\": 5,\\n            \\\"depth_score\\\": 4,\\n            \\\"confidence_score\\\": 5\\n          },\\n          {\\n            \\\"follow_up_question\\\": \\\"How did you prevent similar mistakes from happening in the future?\\\",\\n            \\\"candidate_response\\\": \\\"We implemented stricter access controls and automated backup procedures.\\\",\\n            \\\"relevance_score\\\": 5,\\n            \\\"depth_score\\\": 4,\\n            \\\"confidence_score\\\": 5\\n          }\\n        ]\\n      },\\n      {\\n        \\\"question\\\": \\\"Describe a project where you had to work under pressure to meet a tight deadline. How did you manage your time and prioritize tasks?\\\",\\n        \\\"candidate_response\\\": \\\"We had to launch a new feature within a month.\\\",\\n        \\\"relevance_score\\\": 5,\\n        \\\"depth_score\\\": 3,\\n        \\\"confidence_score\\\": 5,\\n        \\\"follow_up_responses\\\": [\\n          {\\n            \\\"follow_up_question\\\": \\\"What strategies did you use to stay organized and focused?\\\",\\n            \\\"candidate_response\\\": \\\"I created a detailed project plan, broke down the work into smaller tasks, and tracked progress using a Kanban board.\\\",\\n            \\\"relevance_score\\\": 5,\\n            \\\"depth_score\\\": 4,\\n            \\\"confidence_score\\\": 5\\n          },\\n          {\\n            \\\"follow_up_question\\\": \\\"How did you communicate with your team members and stakeholders during the project?\\\",\\n            \\\"candidate_response\\\": \\\"I held daily stand-up meetings and provided regular status updates to stakeholders.\\\",\\n            \\\"relevance_score\\\": 5,\\n            \\\"depth_score\\\": 4,\\n            \\\"confidence_score\\\": 5\\n          },\\n          {\\n            \\\"follow_up_question\\\": \\\"What was the outcome of the project, and what did you learn from the experience?\\\",\\n            \\\"candidate_response\\\": \\\"We launched the feature on time. I learned the importance of planning, communication, and collaboration.\\\",\\n            \\\"relevance_score\\\": 5,\\n            \\\"depth_score\\\": 4,\\n            \\\"confidence_score\\\": 5\\n          }\\n        ]\\n      },\\n      {\\n        \\\"question\\\": \\\"Give an example of when you went above and beyond what was expected of you in a project or task.\\\",\\n        \\\"candidate_response\\\": \\\"I automated a manual testing process.\\\",\\n        \\\"relevance_score\\\": 5,\\n        \\\"depth_score\\\": 3,\\n        \\\"confidence_score\\\": 5,\\n        \\\"follow_up_responses\\\": [\\n          {\\n            \\\"follow_up_question\\\": \\\"What motivated you to go above and beyond?\\\",\\n            \\\"candidate_response\\\": \\\"I wanted to improve the efficiency and accuracy of the testing process.\\\",\\n            \\\"relevance_score\\\": 5,\\n            \\\"depth_score\\\": 4,\\n            \\\"confidence_score\\\": 5\\n          },\\n